                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <origDate notBefore="1796" notAfter="1799">1796–1799</origDate>. 
                            The manuscript was donated to the church <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS1016CelaMaryam">Č̣ǝlā Māryām</placeName> by <persName role="donor" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14498HamaraKidan">wayzāro Ḥamara Kidān</persName>. According to M. Chaîne, prayers contained in the manuscript mention the metropolitan 
                            <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10450YosabI">ʾIyosāb (II)</persName> (in tenure 1770–1803) and 
                            <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8422Salomon">King Salomon (II)</persName> (ruled 1796–1797 and 1799).</origin>
                        <provenance> The manuscript was acquired by <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1071dAbbadi">Antoine d'Abbadie</persName>, sometime between
                                <date>1840</date> and <date>1848</date>. </provenance>
                        <acquisition>The manuscript entered <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0303BNF">Bibliothèque nationale de France</placeName> in
                                <date>1902</date>.</acquisition>
                    </history>
